The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 IPTV comes live on city screen

 A STAFF REPORTER

 S.K. Chakravarty (right) with R. Bandyopadhyay, additional secretary, department of telecommunications, in Calcutta on Tuesday. Picture by Kishor Roy Chowdhury

 Calcutta, Aug. 14: BSNL has launched its IPTV (Internet protocol television) services in the city at an investment of Rs 60 crore.

 The telecom PSU has set a target of 1.75 lakh subscribers in the city by the year-end.

 The installation charges of IPTV are much lower than other options available in the market. We expect a positive response from our customers. There is also a special introductory offer of free recharge coupons worth Rs 2,000 for every BSNL mobile connection, said S.K. Chakravarty, chief general manager, Calcutta Telephones, BSNL.

 IPTV was also launched in Bangalore today. The services are already available in Pune, Mumbai and New Delhi. 




